Targeted (entity) sentiment identification!¶

Here we will do NER based sentiment analysis.

In [11]:
def get_entities_labels(df, topic, sentiment):
    def get_entities_labels(v, entities, labels):
        if v:
            r = [(x,y) for x,y in v]
            for x,y in r:
                entities.append(x)
                labels.append(y)
    entities = []
    labels = []
    df1 = df[(df['topic'] == topic) & (df['sentiment'] == sentiment)]
    df1['NER'].apply(lambda v: get_entities_labels(v, entities, labels))
    df1_sent = pd.DataFrame({'entities':entities,'labels':labels})
    return df1_sent

clean_counts() function gets counts of Named Entities from NER and combines top 100 similar entities based on cosine similarity

In [12]:
def clean_counts(df1, labels, sentiment):
    df_ner = df1.loc[df1.labels == labels, 'entities'].value_counts().reset_index().rename(columns={'index': 'entities',
                                                                                           'entities': 'counts'+sentiment})
    df_ner['entities'] = df_ner['entities'].str.lower()
    df_ner = df_ner[~df_ner['entities'].str.contains('cat')]
    df_ner.reset_index(drop=True, inplace = True)
    df_ner = df_ner.head(100)

    
    corpus = list(df_ner["entities"].values)
    vectorizer = TfidfVectorizer()
    X = vectorizer.fit_transform(corpus)

    df_ner['entities_clean'] = np.NaN
    threshold = 0.6
    for x in range(0,X.shape[0]):
        for y in range(x,X.shape[0]):
            if(x!=y):
                if(cosine_similarity(X[x],X[y])>threshold):
                    if pd.isnull(df_ner.loc[x, 'entities_clean']):
                        df_ner.loc[x, 'entities_clean'] = df_ner.loc[x, 'entities']
                        df_ner.loc[y, 'entities_clean'] = df_ner.loc[x, 'entities']
                    else:
                        df_ner.loc[y, 'entities_clean'] = df_ner.loc[x, 'entities_clean']

    df_ner['entities_clean'].fillna(df_ner['entities'], inplace= True)
    df_ner = df_ner.groupby('entities_clean')['counts'+sentiment].sum().reset_index()
    df_ner = df_ner.sort_values('counts'+sentiment, ascending= False).reset_index(drop = True)

    return df_ner

In [13]:
topic = 1
label = 'ORG'

df1 = get_entities_labels(df, topic, 'Positive')
df_pos = clean_counts(df1, label, 'Positive')

df1 = get_entities_labels(df, topic, 'Negative')
df_neg = clean_counts(df1, label, 'Negative')

df2 = df_pos.merge(df_neg, 'outer')
